# Project: Job Application Assistant Chrome Extension

## Overview
Chrome extension for automating job applications on jobs.lever.co with AI-powered CV-job matching and form auto-fill using DeepSeek (OpenAI-compatible API).

## Tech Stack
- Chrome Extension Manifest V3
- Vanilla JavaScript (no framework)
- OpenAI-compatible API (Sumopod, OpenRouter, DeepSeek, OpenAI, etc.) for AI operations
- Chrome Storage API (storage.local)
- Markdown file for CV/reference data

## Core Features
1. **Match Scoring** - On job posting pages, display weighted multi-parameter match score comparing CV to job description
2. **Form Auto-Fill** - On apply pages, auto-fill fields using profile data + AI-generated answers for open-ended questions

## Architecture
- `/manifest.json` - Extension manifest (MV3)
- `/content/` - Content scripts injected into lever.co pages
  - `content.js` - Main orchestrator/URL router
  - `jd-extractor.js` - Extracts job description from posting page
  - `match-scorer.js` - UI floating panel for score display
  - `form-filler.js` - Detects and fills Lever form fields
- `/background/` - Service worker
  - `service-worker.js` - DeepSeek API calls, storage management
- `/popup/` - Quick controls panel
- `/options/` - Full settings page (API config, CV upload, profile defaults)
- `/lib/` - Shared utilities
  - `storage.js` - Chrome storage wrapper

## Key Rules
- All AI calls go through background service worker via chrome.runtime.sendMessage
- Content scripts communicate with background using message passing
- CV/reference stored as single Markdown file in chrome.storage.local
- DeepSeek API config configured in Options page (base URL, key, model)
- Match scoring uses 6 weighted parameters (Skills 35%, Experience 25%, Domain Knowledge 15%, Cultural Fit 10%, Growth Potential 10%, Background 5%)
- Auto-fill triggered by user button click, not automatic
- Each filled field gets a source badge: [Profile] or [AI]

## File Naming
- All extension code in root folder
- Content scripts in /content/
- Background in /background/
- Options page in /options/
- Popup in /popup/
- Libraries in /lib/

## Prompt Templates

### Match Scoring System Prompt
```
You are a career assessment assistant. Analyze how well the candidate's CV matches the job description. For each dimension, provide a score (0-100) with a one-sentence rationale. Then provide an overall weighted score and 2-3 sentence summary.
Dimensions and weights:
- Skills Match (35%): Technical skills, tools, methodologies alignment
- Experience Level (25%): Years, seniority, scope
- Domain Knowledge (15%): Industry-specific relevance
- Cultural Fit Signals (10%): Communication style, values, work preferences
- Growth Potential (10%): Learning trajectory, adaptability
- Background Alignment (5%): Education, certifications
Return as JSON with fields: skillsMatch, experienceLevel, domainKnowledge, culturalFit, growthPotential, backgroundAlignment, overallScore, summary
```

### Open-Ended Question System Prompt
```
You are a job application assistant. Using the candidate's CV and reference information as context, answer the following job application question concisely and professionally (2-4 sentences). Be specific to the candidate's experience and avoid generic responses.
```

## Lever.co DOM Structure (jobs.lever.co)
- JD Page: `jobs.lever.co/{company}/{posting-id}`
  - Title: `.posting-headline h2`
  - Description: `.posting-description`
  - Categories: `.posting-categories`
- Apply Page: `jobs.lever.co/{company}/{posting-id}/apply`
  - Form: `#application-form`
  - Text inputs: `input[type="text"]`, `input[type="email"]`
  - Selects: `.application-dropdown select`
  - Checkboxes: `input[type="checkbox"]`
  - Radios: `input[type="radio"]`
  - Textareas: `textarea`
  - Custom questions: `.custom-question`
  - Question labels: `.application-label .text`
  - Submit: `button[type="submit"]`